Description: Body sherd of probably Milesian pre-Fikellura pottery cup; white slip; interior, from outside edge: dot rosette; two bands; part of lotus flower; exterior: undetermined decorative motif above two bands; on lower wall, brown band with trace of black below.
Bibliographic references: CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (p. 13, no. 2, pl. 13, no. 2)
Walter-Karydi 1973 / Samische Gefässe des 6. Jahrhunderts vor Christi: Landschaftsstile ostgriechischer Gefässe (p. 47, fig. 86)
Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 248, no. 2)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.866)
